23. sparges. This picture of Septimius weeping as he collects in an urn the warm ashes, all that remain of his deceased friend, is rather comic than pathetic. Probably Septimius, in offering to accompany Horace to Spain, had pointed out the advantage it would be to Horace to have a friend at hand in case of fatal accidents.
